AttackCampaignID: string; Unique identifier of the attack campaign that this packet was a part of, if any.
AttackID: string; Unique identifier of the mitigation that matched the packet, if any.
AttackVector: string; Descriptive name of the type of attack that this packet was a part of, if any. Only for packets matching rules contained within the Cloudflare L3/4 managed ruleset.
ColoCity: string; The city where the Cloudflare data center that received the packet is located.
ColoCode: string; The Cloudflare data center that received the packet (nearest IATA airport code).
ColoCountry: string; The country where the Cloudflare data center that received the packet is located (ISO 3166-1 alpha-2).
ColoGeoHash: string; The latitude and longitude where the Cloudflare data center that received the packet is located (Geohash encoding).
ColoName: string; The unique site identifier of the Cloudflare data center that received the packet (for example, 'ams01', 'sjc01', 'lhr01').
Datetime: int or string; The date and time the event occurred at the edge.
DestinationASN: int; The ASN associated with the destination IP of the packet.
DestinationASNName: string; The name of the ASN associated with the destination IP of the packet.
DestinationCountry: string; The country where the destination IP of the packet is located (ISO 3166-1 alpha-2).
DestinationGeoHash: string; The latitude and longitude where the destination IP of the packet is located (Geohash encoding).
DestinationPort: int; Value of the Destination Port header field in the TCP or UDP packet.
Direction: string; The direction in relation to customer network. Possible values are ingress | egress.
GREChecksum: int; Value of the Checksum header field in the GRE packet.
GREEtherType: int; Value of the EtherType header field in the GRE packet.
GREHeaderLength: int; Length of the GRE packet header, in bytes.
GREKey: int; Value of the Key header field in the GRE packet.
GRESequenceNumber: int; Value of the Sequence Number header field in the GRE packet.
GREVersion: int; Value of the Version header field in the GRE packet.
ICMPChecksum: int; Value of the Checksum header field in the ICMP packet.
ICMPCode: int; Value of the Code header field in the ICMP packet.
ICMPType: int; Value of the Type header field in the ICMP packet.
IPDestinationAddress: string; Value of the Destination Address header field in the IPv4 or IPv6 packet.
IPDestinationSubnet: string; Computed subnet of the Destination Address header field in the IPv4 or IPv6 packet (/24 for IPv4; /64 for IPv6).
IPFragmentOffset: int; Value of the Fragment Offset header field in the IPv4 or IPv6 packet.
IPHeaderLength: int; Length of the IPv4 or IPv6 packet header, in bytes.
IPMoreFragments: int; Value of the More Fragments header field in the IPv4 or IPv6 packet.
IPProtocol: int; Value of the Protocol header field in the IPv4 or IPv6 packet.
IPProtocolName: string; Name of the protocol specified by the Protocol header field in the IPv4 or IPv6 packet.
IPSourceAddress: string; Value of the Source Address header field in the IPv4 or IPv6 packet.
IPSourceSubnet: string; Computed subnet of the Source Address header field in the IPv4 or IPv6 packet (/24 for IPv4; /64 for IPv6).
IPTTL: int; Value of the TTL header field in the IPv4 packet or the Hop Limit header field in the IPv6 packet.
IPTTLBuckets: int; Value of the TTL header field in the IPv4 packet or the Hop Limit header field in the IPv6 packet, with the last digit truncated.
IPTotalLength: int; Total length of the IPv4 or IPv6 packet, in bytes.
IPTotalLengthBuckets: int; Total length of the IPv4 or IPv6 packet, in bytes, with the last two digits truncated.
IPv4Checksum: int; Value of the Checksum header field in the IPv4 packet.
IPv4DSCP: int; Value of the Differentiated Services Code Point header field in the IPv4 packet.
IPv4DontFragment: int; Value of the Don't Fragment header field in the IPv4 packet.
IPv4ECN: int; Value of the Explicit Congestion Notification header field in the IPv4 packet.
IPv4Identification: int; Value of the Identification header field in the IPv4 packet.
IPv4Options: string; List of Options numbers included in the IPv4 packet header.
IPv6DSCP: int; Value of the Differentiated Services Code Point header field in the IPv6 packet.
IPv6ECN: int; Value of the Explicit Congestion Notification header field in the IPv6 packet.
IPv6ExtensionHeaders: string; List of Extension Header numbers included in the IPv6 packet header.
IPv6FlowLabel: int; Value of the Flow Label header field in the IPv6 packet.
IPv6Identification: int; Value of the Identification extension header field in the IPv6 packet.
MitigationReason: string; Reason for applying a mitigation to the packet, if any. Possible values are BLOCKED | RATE_LIMITED |UNEXPECTED | CHALLENGE_NEEDED | CHALLENGE_PASSED | NOT_FOUND | OUT_OF_SEQUENCE | ALREADY_CLOSED.
MitigationScope: string; Whether the packet matched a local or global mitigation, if any. Possible values are local | global.
MitigationSystem: string; Which Cloudflare system sampled the packet. Possible values are dosd | flowtrackd | magic-firewall.
Outcome: string; The action that Cloudflare systems took on the packet. Possible values are pass | drop.
ProtocolState: string; State of the packet in the context of the protocol, if any. Possible values are OPEN | NEW | CLOSING | CLOSED.
RuleID: string; Unique identifier of the rule contained within the Cloudflare L3/4 managed ruleset that this packet matched, if any.
RuleName: string; Human-readable name of the rule contained within the Cloudflare L3/4 managed ruleset that this packet matched, if any.
RulesetID: string; Unique identifier of the Cloudflare L3/4 managed ruleset containing the rule that this packet matched, if any. Possible values are 3b64149bfa6e4220bbbc2bd6db589552.
RulesetOverrideID: string; Unique identifier of the rule within the accounts root ddos_l4 phase ruleset which resulted in an override of the default sensitivity or action being applied/evaluated, if any.
SampleInterval: int; The sample interval is the inverse of the sample rate. For example, a sample interval of 1000 means that this packet was randomly sampled from 1 in 1000 packets. Sample rates are dynamic and based on the volume of traffic.
SourceASN: int; The ASN associated with the source IP of the packet.
SourceASNName: string; The name of the ASN associated with the source IP of the packet.
SourceCountry: string; The country where the source IP of the packet is located (ISO 3166-1 alpha-2).
SourceGeoHash: string; The latitude and longitude where the source IP of the packet is located (Geohash encoding).
SourcePort: int; Value of the Source Port header field in the TCP or UDP packet.
TCPAcknowledgementNumber: int; Value of the Acknowledgement Number header field in the TCP packet.
TCPChecksum: int; Value of the Checksum header field in the TCP packet.
TCPDataOffset: int; Value of the Data Offset header field in the TCP packet.
TCPFlags: int; Value of the Flags header field in the TCP packet.
TCPFlagsString: string; Human-readable string representation of the Flags header field in the TCP packet.
TCPMSS: int; Value of the MSS option header field in the TCP packet.
TCPOptions: string; List of Options numbers included in the TCP packet header.
TCPSACKBlocks: string; List of the SACK Blocks option header in the TCP packet.
TCPSACKPermitted: int; Value of the SACK Permitted option header in the TCP packet.
TCPSequenceNumber: int; Value of the Sequence Number header field in the TCP packet.
TCPTimestampECR: int; Value of the Timestamp Echo Reply option header in the TCP packet.
TCPTimestampValue: int; Value of the Timestamp option header in the TCP packet.
TCPUrgentPointer: int; Value of the Urgent Pointer header field in the TCP packet.
TCPWindowScale: int; Value of the Window Scale option header in the TCP packet.
TCPWindowSize: int; Value of the Window Size header field in the TCP packet.
UDPChecksum: int; Value of the Checksum header field in the UDP packet.
UDPPayloadLength: int; Value of the Payload Length header field in the UDP packet.
Verdict: string; The action that Cloudflare systems think should be taken on the packet. Possible values are pass | drop.
